            Economic Turbulence and Financial Literacy. 
           Nigeria, Africa's largest economy, has faced significant economic challenges in recent years. The COVID-19 pandemic exacerbated existing issues, leading to a recession in 2020, with a GDP contraction of 1.8%. Although the economy has shown signs of recovery, the inflation rate remains alarmingly high, hovering around 16%, and unemployment rates have surged to over 33%. These statistics are more than just numbers; they translate to real-life struggles for millions of Nigerians.<br><br>
           
